cuems-wsclient (0.2.5-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * shelly-mjs: replace em-dash (U+2014) with `--` in the formitgo.local
    migration comment. Shelly's Script.PutCode RPC rejects any non-ASCII
    byte with `-103: Missing or bad argument 'code'!`, which trips
    install_shelly_mjs.py's pre-flight ASCII validator. Same gotcha as
    the original mJS template introduction; the rule still holds —
    keep this file ASCII-only.

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Fri, 29 May 2026 21:46:00 +0200

cuems-wsclient (0.2.4-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * shelly-mjs template: default BRIDGE to http://controller.local:8478
    (avahi alias) instead of the raw bond0 IP. The previous "use the IP,
    not .local" advice was wrong — verified end-to-end on real hardware
    that Shelly's mJS HTTP client resolves controller.local cleanly.
    Hard-coding the IP fails on the production cluster because bond0
    takes DHCP if available and only falls back to the static lease,
    so the IP shifts across boots. install_shelly_mjs.py updated to
    match the new template literal so --bridge patching still works.

